# NOTE: when this file exists, EAS uses it INSTEAD of .gitignore — so it must
# also exclude node_modules and build output, not just the non-mobile dirs.
# EAS Build only needs the Expo app in mobile/ (self-contained: own package-lock).

# SECRETS — MUST STAY FIRST.
# This file REPLACES .gitignore for EAS uploads, so anything gitignored but not
# listed here is still packed into the build archive and shipped to Expo's
# servers. `.secrets/` holds Apple .p8 keys, the production env file and prod DB
# dumps; it is gitignored but was NOT excluded here, so every `eas build`
# uploaded it. Never remove these lines.
.secrets/
**/.secrets/
.env
.env.*
**/.env
**/.env.*
*.p8
*.p12
*.pem
*.key
*.keystore
*.jks
.vercel/
**/.vercel/
_scratch/
archive/
media/
.agents/

# heavy build/deps (normally covered by .gitignore)
node_modules/
mobile/node_modules/
**/node_modules/
.expo/
mobile/.expo/
dist/
mobile/dist/
web-build/
.next/
**/.next/
*.log

# the rest of the monorepo — irrelevant to the mobile app build
/web/
/ios/
/android/
/move/
/infra/
/cli/
/docs/
/marketing/
/.github/
/.claude/
*.mp4
*.mov
